INSERT INTO `e_news` VALUES ('4', 'Blockchain will bring about 10 industry changes ', 'For those unfamiliar with the blockchain, this seems like a small improvement, but in fact the blockchain will bring real change to the way we process information.', '<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">According to the July 23 article of the Spanish newspaper &quot;The News&quot;, in short, the blockchain is a way to encrypt information, which can be used to create a decentralized database, only if you have a key that authorizes the information. To be able to access.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">For those unfamiliar with the blockchain, this seems like a small improvement, but in fact the blockchain will bring real change to the way we process information.</span></p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"http://site.cathkid.com/upload/1532513411FOREIGN201802091331000574319197679.jpg\"/></p><p><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The blockchain will have a greater impact on some industries than other industries. The following are the 10 industries or sectors most affected by blockchain technology:</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">1.Banking industry</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">If transfers and other financial operations are possible between individuals, most of the bank&#39;s intermediary service roles will be challenged by the blockchain. The development of blockchain will lead to a variety of technology finance companies that will provide banking services without the huge infrastructure of traditional banks.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">2. Medical</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Medical records are an indispensable confidential medical document. The preservation and management of medical records is a headache for all medical institutions. The blockchain gives doctors a safe and convenient access to the unique full medical record of each patient. In addition, doctors can immediately grasp the patient&#39;s medical information at any time, which is very important in the rescue.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">3. Food supply</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The blockchain will be a very useful tool to ensure food traceability, which will help to immediately withdraw any food items with safety hazards from the supply process in a more precise manner. It will also help consumers understand more clearly the ingredients and sources of food.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">4. Politics</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">With blockchain technology, electoral fraud that plagues many countries will become a thing of the past. Statistics on overseas referendums will not be controversial. The blockchain will make a series of processes such as voter registration, authentication, and counting of votes more secure and difficult to invade and falsify.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">5. Real estate market</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">With the development of the blockchain, the role of real estate agencies, especially in terms of paperwork, will be weakened. The blockchain simplifies the real estate transaction process and designs smart contracts that only take effect when certain conditions are met. In addition, all documents can be kept in the competent authority.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">6. Law</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The blockchain makes it easier for the legal profession to work and more securely complete all the work related to storing, retrieving, and verifying the source of the document. Many litigation cases, especially those related to inheritance and transactions, will be easier to resolve.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">7. Network security</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Logically speaking, the network security industry will be greatly affected by the blockchain boom. Decentralized data stored in a cloud database can be avoided by hackers. Advanced encryption based on blockchain can create data encryption methods that can hardly be compromised.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">8. Lease</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">All types of leasing businesses, including homes, cars and machinery, can achieve safer transactions through blockchains and foster a network of devices and services between individuals without the need for an intermediary platform such as Uber and Airbnb.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">9. Charity</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Various scandals have made people no longer trust the various non-profit organizations that raise donations, but the blockchain can increase the security of donations and uses.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">10. Education</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The blockchain will revolutionize the education industry, at least in its administrative business. The blockchain-based system gives schools and teachers easy access to student profiles and transcripts. Student information can also be transmitted quickly between different educational institutions.</span></p><p><br/></p>', '2018-05-10', '/upload/15326750351532513411FOREIGN201802091331000574319197679.jpg');
INSERT INTO `e_news` VALUES ('5', 'Blockchain + Supply Chain - a trillion dollar blockchain market', 'There are already many use cases in the supply chain combined with blockchain, which are of great help to reshape the supply chain industry. ', '<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">There are already many use cases in the supply chain combined with blockchain, which are of great help to reshape the supply chain industry. For example, the blockchain allows small suppliers to have better financing conditions. Many of today&#39;s emerging blockchain applications simply use blockchain technology on existing project entities (such as Uber using blockchains, Airbnb using blockchains, etc.).</span></p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://ss2.baidu.com/6ONYsjip0QIZ8tyhnq/it/u=2073848666,3396391840&fm=173&s=BA95AD4C04520BC64D9F2109030070DA&w=640&h=384&img.JPEG\"/></p><p><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">While these projects are also valuable, the “killer” blockchain application shouldn&#39;t simply put existing projects on the blockchain shell and try to make yourself more efficient. These &quot;killer&quot; applications should be to rewrite the industry with blockchain technology. For example, Amazon is not only an online Wal-Mart; it takes advantage of the lack of shelf space to provide customers with more choices than Wal-Mart stores. Google is also not a large Du Wei decimal site, it draws on network hyperlinks and traceable features to promote more efficient information search and mining. So we have every reason to believe that the same thing will happen in the blockchain, and killer apps will change the world.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">We can&#39;t predict exactly what these killer apps are, but one of the most important blockchain applications I&#39;ve heard is to make existing assets pass through the blockchain in the supply chain. This allows any commercial body to put their existing assets (such as real estate, physical investment, etc.) on the blockchain, borrowing funds at very low interest rates, and promoting business growth. If this is possible, the use of the supply chain in the blockchain has the potential to break the existing billionaire market and dramatically change the corporate blueprint. Although it may be that we are far from the mainstream of this application, it may be within 10 years, but such applications show the true potential of blockchain technology.</span></p><p><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Let&#39;s take a quick look at the history and current state of the supply chain industry, and then see how the blockchain subverts it.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">A brief history of the supply chain industry</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The industrial era began with centralized production. Ford, mass production and Taylorism have helped centralize production more efficiently. This centralization uses a large production plant to complete the production of raw materials to the final product in the factory. Ford produces cars in a few factories, producing vehicles through rubber and iron.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">After the Second World War, things went to the second stage, and enterprises were more centralized, not only in production, but also in finance.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">By getting better terms from suppliers, companies become similar to banks, get cheap assets and sell them to companies in developing countries, and companies in these countries simply cannot compete because of their capital costs. It is much higher.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The third stage is the centralization of risk. According to the idea of hedge funds, investment is likely to be zero-risk because anything will be hedged. They are convinced that if some industries decline, then the other part will grow. At the end of the 21st century, these large companies thought that all their money was risk free.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">However, this centralized mode works well only if the system does not fluctuate significantly. If the system has a lot of shocks, then the crisis will spread quickly, which will lead to the global financial crisis of 2009.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Today, the supply chain industry accounts for two-thirds of global GDP (about 54 trillion globally) and is the industry with the most employees in the world.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The main reason for the inefficiency of this industry is the relatively high degree of centralization. Industry tycoons (such as Wal-Mart and Starbucks) have got very good terms from suppliers because they control a lot of purchasing power. This means that the closer you are to these tycoons in the supply chain, the less cash you will get. These suppliers will give industry tycoons better terms and often do not get loans. However, these issues are the areas with the greatest growth potential, and these growths will have great significance.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">For example, a small coffee farmer in Africa cannot expand his farm because he has to give the import and export company the best terms, the import and export company has to give the processor the best terms, and the processor has to give Starbucks the best terms. .</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Starbucks may be able to get $1 billion with only 3% interest, but African coffee farmers may get a $500 loan with 20% interest. Then, Starbucks can invest in products that only need 1 million down payments and have a 10% return. The coffee farmer can&#39;t get enough loans to expand production, even if he can, and count the interest cost, he has no money.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The end result is that all assets are in Starbucks, but it is difficult to add value. Although small farmers have the potential to add value to assets, they have no ability to acquire assets.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">In a more stable environment, centralization is actually effective, but in an unstable and rapidly changing environment, weak centralization is actually more adaptable and has better &quot;economic rationality.&quot;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">In today&#39;s world, the way the supply chain industry operates has become less effective, and even counterproductive.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">According to economist Ronald Coase, as information becomes more easily spread, the size of the company should be smaller, and the supply chain should be made up of many smaller companies that are more likely to adapt to change.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">In a way, this situation will change. More and more companies are looking for outsourcing companies or online freelance markets, such as Upwork, to find some parts of their supply chain.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">However, this shift is much slower than overall economic growth, as large companies get cheap assets to buy small companies and then use them inefficiently.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Capital is always in a good position because capital is relatively more scarce: valuable assets are always short of money.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">There are about $700 trillion in assets in the world, but there are only 70 trillion dollars in legal currency, and perhaps another 100 trillion in stocks and financial products.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">This means that people have to work hard to get this 170 trillion in cash. (including legal currency, stocks and financial products)</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">In the current situation, cash needs to go from big companies to small and medium-sized companies to individual farmers. But blockchain technology uses tokens to smooth out gaps between existing and value assets. This will give small, fast-growing companies, such as coffee farmers, access to funds at an acceptable rate.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Blockchain in the supply chain industry case</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">In fact, in history, using assets you own, such as a house, can be exchanged for soft exchanges that do not endorse gold or other hard assets. In the Middle Ages, banks could issue their own credentials or the Pharaoh would give you hieroglyphs thousands of years ago.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">This is actually what the token has to do. However, the biggest difference with blockchain technology is that once your assets are placed on the blockchain, there are many decentralized nodes to maintain the ledger, and the subject of the issued credential no longer needs third-party trust. .</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The following is the flow of the entire blockchain system. Suppose you get a loan through the equity of the house. You need to have a legal contract to put the property of the house on the blockchain, and the terms say that if you don&#39;t repay the loan, the ownership of the house will be transferred to the collateral. Then, you can use the house as a guarantee to create your own pass on the blockchain. But once your assets are in the chain, there will be a contract saying: &quot;You can&#39;t sell the property until you have repaid all the passes I have issued.&quot; Then you can go to the exchange to talk about the pass in exchange for what you think is better than Other passes or legal currency or other assets that are more valuable to the property. And you don&#39;t have to pay interest personally because there are no third parties like banks in the whole transaction. You actually take the loan from yourself, so of course you don&#39;t have to give yourself interest as you give the bank a monthly payment.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The same mechanism can be used for all asset-based lending. The world&#39;s assets are worth $700 trillion, and they can all be converted into asset-backed currencies to create higher liquidity, ensuring access to funds where it is most needed, such as African coffee farmers.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Assuming coffee farmers buy new equipment, production can increase by 30%. Now he can&#39;t find capital to invest in these devices. However, if he can use the current farm assets as collateral to borrow on the blockchain, he can buy new equipment, increase production, and pay for the loan through increased profits. And this will not increase the amount of legal currency, it is necessary to know that the legal currency is very scarce. The transparency of the blockchain also reduces the risk for investors, who will clearly see the orders from Starbucks on the blockchain to buy these coffees, and because of the relatively low risk, they can also lower interest rates. Lending funds.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The blockchain separates the map from the area. But in fact, the blockchain (map) reflects the real world (region), you can safely think that the two are actually the same, all capital providers will borrow with less risk. The supply chain industry accounts for 54 trillion of global GDP, and the small growth of this industry will lead to a significant growth in the global economy.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The blockchain, which provides low interest rates and endorsement of assets, will definitely change the structure of the global economy. This will make small businesses in developed countries more competitive and create more jobs. Most importantly, blockchain can help developing countries find ways to invest in their own businesses and help them escape poverty.</span></p><p><br/></p>', '2018-05-21', '/upload/1532675830u=2073848666,3396391840&fm=173&s=BA95AD4C04520BC64D9F2109030070DA&w=640&h=384&img.JPEG');
INSERT INTO `e_news` VALUES ('6', 'How does the blockchain drive supply chain innovation? ', 'To discuss the supply chain based on the blockchain, we must first look at the characteristics of the blockchain. ', '<p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">To discuss the supply chain based on the blockchain, we must first look at the characteristics of the blockchain. A blockchain is a technology that allows for authenticated data communication between each participant in the supply chain without the need for an intermediate &quot;trusted central organization.&quot;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">By verifying and adding data in real time, blockchain can increase the transparency of the entire supply chain. According to the Bank of England, blockchain is &quot;a technology that allows unidentified people to trust each other&#39;s shared event records.&quot;</span></p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"/ueditor/php/upload/image/20180727/1532677490880547.jpg\" alt=\"âä¾åºé¾âçå¾çæç´¢ç»æ\" width=\"711\" height=\"379\"/></p><p><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Blockchains can be used to increase the transparency and traceability of materials throughout the supply chain. If every business does not want to exchange information directly, then this approach would be particularly valuable without a “central trust”.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">In addition, as consumers demand more transparency and increasing supply chain complexity, blockchain technology is an effective and low-cost way to track every material used in the final product. Moreover, it is important to build consumer confidence in the market environment and social awareness.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Through market theory analysis, we have the following summary:</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">1) Several ways in which the blockchain improves the supply chain:</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Improve the visibility of materials throughout the supply chain;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Reduce management costs;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Identification of counterfeit products.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">2) Current challenges</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Blockchain technology is still in the early stages of the supply chain;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The industry is still exploring security, cost and impact;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">It is still difficult to connect blockchains to physical objects;</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The technical complexity has not yet convinced all stakeholders to block the blockchain.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">3) Suggestions:</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Companies should continue to monitor the progress of the blockchain, which helps to improve supply chain transparency and provide new opportunities to reduce procurement risk, reduce management costs, and improve stakeholder engagement.</span></p><p><br/></p>', '2018-06-05', '/upload/1532677439567003a6c363f9755226e7a4118d1ba7.jpg');
INSERT INTO `e_news` VALUES ('7', 'Blockchain plus supply chain, reshaping the supply chain system ', 'The “blockchain+” revolution has begun in the medical, financial, and intelligent manufacturing industries, and will undoubtedly have an important impact on the supply chain.', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The “blockchain+” revolution has begun in the medical, financial, and intelligent manufacturing industries, and will undoubtedly have an important impact on the supply chain.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Supply chain management and supply chain finance, because of the large scale of the market, satisfying the characteristics of multi-trust subject, multi-party cooperation, medium and low frequency trading, and complete business logic, are the natural blockchains.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><a style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑; font-size: medium; white-space: normal;\"></a></p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><a style=\"font-family: 微软雅黑; font-size: medium; white-space: normal;\"><img src=\"/ueditor/php/upload/image/20180727/1532677729691418.png\" width=\"598\" height=\"330\"/></a></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">1. Problems in traditional supply chains</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">1.1 Supply chain management spans a large span, information asymmetry</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The current supply chain has a large upstream and downstream span, and there are many enterprises involved. The core enterprises have limited management capabilities and influences on the entire supply chain, and management efficiency has dropped significantly and management costs have risen.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Product production cycles and supply cycles are complicated, fragmented, and geographically dispersed. Traditional technologies and concepts can no longer accommodate today&#39;s commodity production and supply.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The average company can manage suppliers from the 1st to the 2nd level. With the continuous refinement of the global division of labor, the number of suppliers has doubled, expanded and spread all over the world. The core enterprises cannot control the goods flowing from upstream and downstream supply companies in real time.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">In the era of big data, information asymmetry can put companies at a disadvantage and even reduce the value of the entire supply chain ecosystem.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">1.2 Information traceability is weak</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Because of the lack of transparency in the supply chain, there is a lack of effective and reliable ways for buyers and sellers to verify the true value of the products being bought and sold.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">This means that the price paid by the buyer does not truly reflect the cost of the product, which inevitably increases the overall cost of the supply chain.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">At present, the supply chain is still unable to track the source of illegal activities such as counterfeit and shoddy goods, illegal labor, and money laundering in all aspects of the supply chain.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">1.3 Supply chain full chain data acquisition is difficult</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The information systems of the enterprises involved in the supply chain are scattered among different suppliers. The information such as procurement, production, circulation, sales and logistics is completely separated. There is no information platform to store, process, share and analyze such information, which limits the rich data. And the potential value of information, a large amount of information in a state that cannot be collected or accessed.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">At the same time, it is difficult to check and review these information, the information exchange is not smooth, and manual re-reconciliation is required, which also increases the audit cost of transaction payment and billing period.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">2. Blockchain + supply chain can solve many problems</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">2.1 Information is updated in real time to eliminate third parties</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">The blockchain can build a platform that includes all supply chain links such as suppliers, manufacturers, distributors, retailers, logistics, etc., on which all companies form alliances, recording logistics, information flow, and capital flow. On the chain, it tracks all the dynamics of the supply chain in real time and achieves synergy.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Make the entire supply chain transparent and visual, and multiple participants per transaction, without the need for third-party intermediaries, can view the same transaction records, verify identity and confirm transactions.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">2.2 Easy to trace</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Change to the book information for the entire life cycle of all participants sharing the transaction. It is based on the state of the information rather than the communication of information. The vague information in the past is now clearly visible.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">At the same time, the blockchain is a publicly issued ledger, and the ledger is a decentralized structural feature. No party has ownership of the ledger, nor can it manipulate the data at will according to its own wishes. The blockchain can produce goods. Trace the source throughout the process.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">2.3 New model of supply chain finance</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">Since the blockchain breaks the data islands of various enterprises, there will be more data sources for the big data in the supply chain, which will greatly improve the stock and quality of the data, so that big data can better play its role. . At the same time, the irreversible modification of blockchain data also enhances the credibility of data, making it possible for companies to use data crediting, thereby promoting the establishment and prosperity of the big data trading market.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px; color: rgb(89, 89, 89);\">In supply chain finance, the ticket platform built with blockchain technology can be combined with supply chain financial services to realize bill financing, issuance, payment bill splitting, statistical reporting, clearing and settlement functions. In the case of multi-party witnesses, the digital bills are openly and transparently fast-paid and quickly split, allowing the credit of core enterprises to pass upstream and downstream of the supply chain, creating a new model of supply chain finance.</span></p><p><br/></p>', '2018-06-15', '/upload/1532677831d3436396156e4feba6195484876621c1.png');
INSERT INTO `e_news` VALUES ('8', 'How to build a supply chain information platform based on blockchain technology? ', 'The blockchain has brought about a great change in the arrival of the digital economy era. ', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">The blockchain has brought about a great change in the arrival of the digital economy era. The blockchain is currently used in the banking, securities, and insurance industries with the highest share. The future blockchain will be developed under the guidance of technology. Continue to accelerate, applications in the supply chain industry will follow, leading to a leap-forward development of the new supply chain industry.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">The use of blockchain technology to build a supply chain information technology platform, mainly using blockchain as the underlying technology, linking supply chain alliances, financial institutions and government regulatory agencies to build a highly integrated autonomous supply chain information platform to promote all aspects of the supply chain Business flow, logistics, capital flow, and information flow are combined to ensure efficient and independent information flow in all links of the supply chain, improve the transparency of information in all aspects of the supply chain, and establish a supply chain mutual trust and win-win ecosystem in an uncertain environment.</span></p><p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size: 20px;\"><strong class=\"ql-font-serif\" style=\"font-family: Georgia, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, serif; box-sizing: border-box;\"><img src=\"https://ss2.baidu.com/6ONYsjip0QIZ8tyhnq/it/u=270594632,1222230245&fm=173&s=FAA3716C480EA55386FF981303001099&w=533&h=300&img.JPEG\" width=\"567\" height=\"331\"/></strong></span></p><p><br/></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">Blockchain type selection</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">The supply chain information system provides services for the participating entities in the supply chain. Therefore, it is necessary to select the appropriate blockchain according to the structural characteristics of the supply chain. The types of blockchains can be divided into public chains and private chains. Private chains can be further subdivided into fully enclosed private chains (also known as pure private chains) and semi-public private chains (also known as federated chains).</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">The public chain is an open system. Anyone can freely become a node in the blockchain and enjoy all the information on the acquisition chain, trade on the chain, participate in consensus, participate in accounting, and maintain the system. And other rights. The private chain has certain closedness. It usually needs to rely on the offline entity organization. The node needs to be approved by the organization and certified by the system to join the blockchain. The nodes in the alliance chain are not completely equal. Only some nodes that have been filtered according to the rules can obtain the right to verify the new block and bookkeeping, and participate in the consensus mechanism on the chain. Therefore, the alliance chain is easier to set up than the public chain control, and the scalability is better. A purely private chain is also known as an internal chain. In a purely private chain, the network is usually built around a central organization. The rights of consensus, verification, and accounting on the blockchain are strictly controlled. Only certain internal entities can conduct transactions, and the remaining nodes usually only have partial reads. s right. Pure private chains are easy to deploy and easy to control.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">However, the public chain transaction speed is too slow, the node entry threshold is too low, the pure private chain is too closed, and the nodes do not have equality. In contrast, the alliance chain has a wide range of applications, and the network part can be realized while ensuring the transaction speed. Decentralization to ensure the immutability of data. Based on the structural characteristics of the supply chain organization, the supply chain information system should choose to use the blockchain technology to form an information platform.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">Various blockchain characteristics</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">Constructing a conceptual model of the Trinity Supply Chain Information Platform</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">The conceptual model of the Trinity Supply Chain Information Platform based on blockchain technology is shown in the figure. Three of them represent the supply chain alliance, financial institutions and government regulatory agencies. The integration represents the information platform with integrated features that can connect these three types of organizations. The peer-to-peer information interaction can be directly realized between any two nodes on the platform. Realize information sharing, collaborative and co-governance, and at the same time realize intelligent supply of products in the supply chain, intelligent financial services and intelligent government regulation through intelligent contracts, and build a trust-and-win supply chain ecosystem in an uncertain external environment. .&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">Conceptual model of Trinity supply chain information platform</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">Supply chain information platform participation subject</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">&nbsp;(1) Supply Chain Alliance: The supply chain alliance usually includes suppliers, manufacturers, distributors, retailers and recyclers. It is the main initiator of the information platform and the main service target of the platform. Alliance members can directly trade with upstream and downstream enterprises in the supply chain through the blockchain information platform, and the transaction information records are packaged as blocks recorded in the platform and stored in a distributed manner. Each member of the system can view the corresponding data in the supply chain at any time according to the information sharing convention, and provide real and reliable data support and basis for the supply chain management decision. At the product circulation level, each product corresponds to a unique electronic ID, from raw material acquisition to finished product output, product information including product distribution, retail to recycling and other supply chain links can be stored in the supply chain information platform through the product&#39;s electronic ID. In the above, the members and the end consumers can check the circulation information of the product in the supply chain according to the agreed authority, thereby ensuring the traceability of the product. At the level of capital circulation, smart contracts embedded in the platform can realize automatic transfer of transaction funds, and automatic execution of claims contracts, which can significantly improve payment efficiency and simplify the liquidation process. Blockchain digital signature and asymmetric encryption technology ensure the reliability of supply chain information. The distributed storage method ensures that information cannot be tampered with, enhances information transparency in the supply chain, and improves the overall trust and competition of the supply chain. force. At the same time, blockchain technology guarantees the standardization of operational processes based on encryption algorithms, can break geographical restrictions, effectively eliminate cultural and monetary barriers between different countries and organizations, and reduce unnecessary friction between nodes. Promote the establishment of a cross-national intercultural credit system.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">(2) Financial institutions: In the process of production and consumption of products, enterprises and consumers in the supply chain will generate many financial needs that are attached to the supply chain. For example, companies in the supply chain usually have financing loans, stock issuance, and crowdfunding. Demand for insurance, accounting, auditing, etc., and consumers will also have to purchase insurance related to products, participate in crowdfunding and purchase stocks in the supply chain. When traditional financial institutions provide financial services to enterprises and consumers in the supply chain, the lack of reliable supply chain transaction information requires a lot of manpower and resources to conduct on-the-spot investigations, and the information obtained may not accurately reflect customer credit. In order to control risks, financial institutions often turn a blind eye to the weak enterprises that really need financial support in the supply chain, which not only brings considerable losses to financial institutions, but also hinders the development of SMEs in the supply chain. The blockchain information platform can truly and completely record the information of business flow, logistics and capital flow in the supply chain, effectively solve the problem of information asymmetry between financial institutions and supply chain enterprises, and bring great convenience to the credit information of financial enterprises. Blockchain technology can help to form innovative supply chain finance services while promoting the smooth development of various supply chain financial services.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">(3) Government supervision: Under the current supervision mechanism, the supervision organization cannot observe the situation of the supervision object in real time, and can only organize the manpower to investigate after a certain time point or a problem occurs in a certain link in the supply chain, and the supervision cost is high. Problems such as low operational efficiency and poor information quality are emerging. If the government regulatory agencies such as the Administration for Industry and Commerce, the Taxation Administration, and the Transportation Administration are connected to the information platform and open the access to specific information to the regulatory authorities, the regulatory authorities can directly write the regulations into the block through smart contract technology. The chain code dynamically supervises all links of business flow, logistics and capital flow in the supply chain, and transforms the traditional single government supervision into the main supervision of the supply chain participants and consumers. In this way, not only can the legal binding force be improved, but also prevent it from happening. Even when there is a problem in the supply chain, the regulatory agency can quickly find the source of the problem through information traceability, and the evidence is convenient and reliable.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">(4) Blockchain maintenance enterprise: Although the supply chain information platform is built by the supply chain alliance, it still needs professional technical companies such as Google and IBM to provide technical support, physical facilities, system construction and daily maintenance as blockchain maintenance enterprises. The supply chain alliance needs to pay the maintenance fee to the maintenance company on a regular basis. As a service provider of the blockchain information system, the blockchain maintenance enterprise does not have access to information. Correspondingly, there is no key to open the information. Only the basic configuration data of the system and the supply chain data after encryption are processed, which greatly reduces the number of links. It risks the disclosure of information about the supply chain.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 20px; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-size: 20px;\">When the blockchain chain supply chain, the supply chain information platform created by the blockchain technology will make the supply chain more transparent, and it is easier to realize large-scale data collaboration and information collaboration. It is conducive to the traceability and security of the supply chain, promotes the safety and reliability of the current and future economy, and quickly takes advantage of the opportunities for development in the era of digital economy, and will lead the economic development of the entire era.</span></p><p><br/></p>', '2018-06-20', '/upload/1532678016u=270594632,1222230245&fm=173&s=FAA3716C480EA55386FF981303001099&w=533&h=300&img.JPEG');

